
Each module has a single "window" for consistency.  This window may
contain the following widgets:

Menu - on the menu bar
IntegerSlider
IntegerDial
IntegerGuage
RealSlider
RealDial
RealGuage
RealThumbwheel
OnOffSwitch
TextInput
FileSelection
RadioBox
MenuSelector
CheckBox
Button
HelpItem
ColorChooser
ColormapChooser
LineGraph
BarGraph
Meter
LEDStack
LCDDisplay
Message


Parameters:
All:
	title - string
All except Menu:
	width - int
	height - int
Menu - on the menu bar:
	nitems - int
	item - n*String
IntegerSlider:
	min - int
	max - int
	value - int
	tickmarks - int
	orientation - enum
	style - enum {Slider, Dial, Guage};
RealSlider: ***
	min - real ***
	max - real ***
	value - real ***
	tickmarks - int
	orientation - enum ***
	style - enum {Slider ***, Dial, Guage, ThumbWheel};
OnOffSwitch: ***
	value - bool ***
	style - enum {Checkbox, Switch***}
TextInput:
	value - string
FileSelection:
	value - string
Exclusive:
	nitems - int
	item - n*string
	selected_item - int
	style - enum { RadioBox, Menubutton, ScrollingList}
Nonexclusive:
	nitems - int
	item - n*string
	selected_items - Special set class
	style - enum { Checkbox, ScrollingList}
Button:
HelpItem:
	Help text
ColorChooser:
	color - color
ColormapChooser:
	colormap - colormap
Meter:  Go into RealSlider???
	min - real
	max - real
	value - real
	autorange - bool
	show_value - bool
	orientation - enum
	enum Style {NeedleMeter, LEDStack };
LCDDisplay:
	text - string
Message:
	text - string
LineGraph:
BarGraph:
	xmin - real
	xmax - real
	ymin - real
	ymax - real
	Each set:
		style - enum {Line, Bar };


Data types:
	string
	int
	real
	int, string pair
	enum
	Set clas
	color
	colormap
	bool
	Dataset